  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "The fragile US-Iran ceasefire is driving a classic relief rally with oil plunging below $100, bonds rallying (yields dropping), dollar weakening below 99, and risk assets surging including Bitcoin above $72K. However, the ceasefire is already showing cracks over Lebanon while FOMC minutes reveal Fed concerns about slower disinflation progress and tariff risks, suggesting this relief may be temporary.",
    "regimeImpact": "This remains a bear market oversold relief rally as the ceasefire fragility and Fed hawkish undertones suggest the fundamental regime drivers (stagflation risks, credit stress) are only temporarily masked.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Continue BMNR cash-secured put ladder as Bitcoin volatility (70K BTC exchange buying, $596M liquidations) creates premium opportunities while maintaining structural $62,300 support",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight as bond rally from ceasefire relief provides temporary cushion but Fed minutes suggest persistent inflation concerns",
      "Prepare to add short exposure on any further relief rally strength as oil below $100 removes immediate stagflation pressure but ceasefire fragility remains high risk"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil drop below $100 removes immediate stagflation threat but Strait of Hormuz closure risks remain elevated with ceasefire fracturing over Lebanon.",
      "Bitcoin $280M bear liquidation squeeze above $72K shows strong momentum but leverage delta instability suggests range-bound volatility ahead.",
      "FOMC minutes reveal 'vast majority' expect slower progress toward 2% inflation target with tariff and oil price upside risks still prominent.",
      "Dollar breaking below 99 and bond yields declining signal risk-on relief rally but participants expect tariff inflation pressure to diminish only later this year."
    ]
  },
